---
By: Edmund Burke
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 373
    Verse: 4
Tags:
  - Power
---
All persons possessing a portion of power ought to be strongly and awfully
impressed with an idea that they act in trust, and that they are to account
for their conduct in that trust to the one great Master, Author, and
Founder of society.
